title: For Sale:  Bushmaster Armpistol
postcontent: This is a Bushmaster (Gwinn) Armpistol.  It was designed as an Air Force aircrew survival weapon.  It is based on the M16/AR15 but uses an AK type piston (long before piston ARs became popular).  It beats AR type pistols hands down because there is no buffer tube and the pistol grip is in front of the magazine, carying the weight over your elbow.  It is easily one of the coolest guns made.  This is a low serial number piece that appears to have been used to try various charging handle locations and has a raised sight that at first looks way high, but allows you to shoot it with the shooting arm locked, supported by the off hand, with the cheek touching your arm, allowing a very steady hold almost like a rifle.  The pistol grip swivels for a comfortable shooting position--again way better than AR type pistols.  It came with a standard flash hider, which is included, but I have place a blast forwarder on it to direct most of the muzzle blast away from the shooter.  A fantastic addition to any collection.  Can meet in Minden or Carson City.

Kimber builds some of the world's finest pistols, right here in America--- something that makes sense as few things are as American as the 1911. The venerable 1911, on its own merit, is an engineering masterpiece. The simple fact that shooters still marvel today over a design that is over 100-years-old speaks volumes about the gun that has stood the test of time. Virtually every critical component on each pistol is manufactured inside the Kimber factory. Only the finest raw materials come through the front gate, and Kimber takes care of the rest. This ensures every component meets unequaled standards. The Kimber Ultra Carry II is a 3" barrel 9mm 1911 paired with a compact frame with stainless finish, and a brush polished black slide. Kimber workmanship and quality are easy to see, even down to the smallest detail. The melded forged stainless steel slide and lightweight aluminum alloy frame fit together with tight tolerances and function perfectly. Recoil on the Kimber Ultra Carry II feels significantly less than that of competing designs. This is due in part to this pistol’s lower center of gravity, which is slightly below the slide, and very close to where the shooter's hand grips the gun. Although the single-stack magazine puts the Kimber's capacity at only eight rounds, the relatively small diameter of the 1911's frame still allow the shooter to create a secure two-handed grip. A match grade barrel and bushing deliver tack driving accuracy. For added reliability, Kimber includes a full- length guide rod, as the shorter G.I. style guide rods have a tendency to bind or break over time. Snag-free, low profile front and rear combat sights sit on top of the slide and provide a consistent target presentation. The checkering on the mainspring housing and the partial checkering of the wood grip feels secure.The knurled extended magazine release of the Kimber Ultra Carry II is a huge improvement over releases seen on other pistols. Performing tactical reloads is quick, simple and efficient. The Kimber Ultra Carry II single stage, match grade aluminum trigger is a joy to pull, especially over the mushy triggers seen on most double action pistols. The 4 – 5 lbs pull is steady and smooth, while the reset is short and crisp. This is a gun that fires naturally, even for beginner's that have “low and left” trigger slap tendencies. In fact, the Kimber Ultra Carry II has one of the smoothest trigger pulls of any production1911 on the market. Other features include a clean, single sided thumb safety. Many shooters actually prefer this style over the bulkier ambidextrous paddles. To further minimize felt recoil, the grip safety is a high-ride designed beavertail that quickly establishes a positive grip for maximum control in stress fire situations. For service and repair, the pistol is backed by a manufacturers 1- year warranty. Overall, the Kimber Ultra Carry II Two Tone in 9mm is a lightweight, low recoil 1911 that is accurate, well-built and engineered for years of reliable service.

title: For Sale/Trade:  KS-47 Rifle, New and Unfired
postcontent: I've got a new, unfired PSA KS-47 rifle for sale. These KS-47s are basically an AR platform that is chambered in 7.62x39, and accepts any AK magazine. Way cheaper to shoot than firing 5.56 or 223, plus much more punch! If you're unfamiliar with these rifles, check out the video on youtube (PSA KS47 -vs- CMMG Mutant).The Palmetto State Armory KS47 is based on the AR15, and combines the modular construction, accuracy and precision of the AR platform with the stopping power and the magazine options of the AK. While the current AR47 fires the 7.62x39 AK round, it uses modified AR-style magazines that are not nearly as plentiful as AK-style magazines, that were optimized for reliable feeding of the 7.62x39 round. The KS47 lets the AK shooter capitalize on his inventory of magazines and ammo with an AR-style platform. Unlike the AK, where the barrel is permanently pressed into the receiver, the KS47 features an AR-style modular configuration which consists of a barreled upper receiver, and a lower receiver that houses the fire control group and magazine. The modular configuration allows customers to have several different barrel configurations with one lower receiver, just by releasing two pins. Lower: The 7075-T6 billet lower receiver is hardcoat anodized, and accepts standard AR15 fire control groups. The extended magazine release is outside of the trigger guard for safety, which allows for an AK-style release movement, but also features oversize side paddles for fingertip release by the trigger finger. Fitted with a Ergo grip and M4-style stock, the receiver also features a standard, mil-spec diameter, 6 position, 7075 carbine buffer tube. The KS47 lower has steel reinforcements to accept AK style surplus magazines including drum-style.Upper: The KS47 hybrid upper receiver is precision machined out of billet 7075 T6 aluminum, and then hardcoat anodized for durability. While retaining the look of a standard M4 upper, the KS47 hybrid upper is designed to work with either the KS47 lower, or the standard AR47 lower. The chrome moly vanadium barrel is chambered in 7.62x39 with a 1 in 10 twist, has M4-style feed ramps, is nitride treated for accuracy and durability, and is finished off with a 5/8-24 thread A2-style compensator. The forward, assist, dust cover, charging handle, and safety are all standard AR15, as is the PSA Slim free-float rail and barrel nut.BCG: The hybrid KS47 Bolt carrier group works with either AK47 magazines or AR47 magazines, and features an extended firing pin. The carrier is made of 8620 steel, chrome lined and phosphate coated, and the chrome lined gas key is attached with grade 8 bolts and properly staked. The Bolt is made of phosphate coated 9310 steel. The KS47 Upper and Hybrid BCG are compatible with standard AR15 lowers for use with AR47-style magazines.I'm asking $900 for the rifle with one steel or PMAG 30 round magazine (buyers choice).   *** Drum magazine in pics is not include with this sell, at this price.
